data.value: Involves tracking and coordinating orders from inception to fulfillment, ensuring efficient processes among teams, software, and partners. The goal is to provide quick, accurate delivery—optimizing business capacity and customer satisfaction through technology-enhanced systems.

data.value: Business process of planning, developing, launching, and managing a product or service. It includes the entire lifecycle of a product, from ideation to development to go to market.

data.name: Security/Role-basedauthorizationDescription
data.value: Role-based access control (RBAC) refers to the idea of assigning permissions to users based on their role within an organization. It offers a simple, manageable approach to access management that is less prone to error than assigning permissions to users individually.

data.name: ShoppingCartManagementDescription
data.value: The fundamental function of an online shopping cart is the ability to add products. Customers might search for your product via a search engine and land on a product page. Or they may search or browse products on your website.

data.name: WebShopTitleDescription
data.value: Online shopping is a form of electronic commerce which allows consumers to directly buy goods or services from a seller over the Internet using a web browser or a mobile app. Consumers find a product of interest by visiting the website of the retailer directly or by searching among alternative vendors using a shopping search engine, which displays the same product's availability and pricing at different e-retailers.
